<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,418,1196,1222]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="43">Fibrodontia brevidens</emphasis>
(Pat.) Hjortstam &amp; Ryvarden
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1273,1454]" pageId="5" pageNumber="43">
This species is characterized by small crowded aculei, encrusted skeletal-like hyphae, and broadly ellipsoid basidiospores. It has a pantropical distribution and is known from 
<collectingCountry box="[980,1058,1312,1338]" name="Brazil" pageId="5" pageNumber="43">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1073,1197,1312,1338]" name="Colombia" pageId="5" pageNumber="43">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1211,1315,1312,1338]" name="Ecuador" pageId="5" pageNumber="43">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1329,1435,1312,1338]" name="Uruguay" pageId="5" pageNumber="43">Uruguay</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Martinez, S. &amp; Nakasone, K. K." box="[161,487,1350,1376]" pageId="5" pageNumber="43" pagination="481 - 484" refId="ref8819" refString="Martinez, S. &amp; Nakasone, K. K. (2011) New records and checklist of corticioid Basidiomycota from Uruguay. Mycotaxon 114: 481 - 484." type="journal article" year="2011">Martínez &amp; Nakasone 2011</bibRefCitation>
), and 
<collectingCountry box="[558,678,1350,1376]" name="Venezuela" pageId="5" pageNumber="43">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
in South America.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
